Install vim CLI on windows
 
  install chocolatey
  choco install vim
  vim --file--
  i (insert)
  (press esc to exit editor mode)
 
  :              (enter cmd mode)
  w              (write)
  q              (quit vim)
  q!             (quit without writing)
  r --filename-- (opens the file in the existing buffer)
  w --newfilename--  

  Normal mode
  u       (undo file)
  0       (line start) $ (line end)
  x       (delete a char)
  dd      (delete a line)
  hjkl    (to move cursor)
  ! --terminalcmd--
